71, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q175038"}], "brief_description": "<p>In the year 2035, convict James Cole reluctantly volunteers to be sent back in time to discover the origin of a deadly virus that wiped out nearly all of the earth’s population and forced the survivors into underground communities.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [{"id": 46, "name": "There's always a lighthouse", "description": "The thaumatrope was an early optical illusion device popular in the Victorian era and was important to the development of the moving image."}], "recommendations": [], "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>Charles Roven</p>", "creator_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "creator_credit_for_label_pa": "", "creator_credit_for_label_hi": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>United States of America, 1995</p>", "headline_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "headline_credit_for_label_pa": "", "headline_credit_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_pa": "", "title_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_override_pa": "", "title_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_for_label_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_pa": "", "description_for_label_hi": "", "description_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_override_pa": "", "description_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": ""}, "description": "<p><i>Bioshock Infinite</i> explores themes of choice, fatalism, predeterminism and the multiple worlds theory. <I>Twelve Monkeys</i> explores similar themes, arguing particularly for hard determinism, the belief that our lives are prewritten and inescapable. Both works feature time traveling to avoid fate.</p>"}, {"id": 183, "start": {"id": 1389, "acmi_id": "tmdb-movie-63", "title": "Twelve Monkeys", "